subanswer.text: Each table costs $38995920. To find out the total price for one set of items where both quantities equal 1 then sum up those prices; thus ($38995920)x(4)+($10)*(3899592)=$155983680+$38995920=Total Price=$194981772. Answer: Total Cost Before Discount = \$194981772
